The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bharti in staff reshuffle

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Aug. 11: Bharti Tele-Ventures Ltd today carried out minor organisational changes following resignation of two senior executives ? Jagdish Kini, executive director of south regional hub, and Madhur Taneja, chief operating officer of Madhya Pradesh.

 Atul Bindal, chief marketing officer and director of mobility, will take over as executive director of the regional mobility hub in the south.

 Sunil K. Goyal, senior vice-president, strategic planning group, will take over as chief operating officer, mobility, for the Madhya Pradesh circle.

 Kini will take a non-operational supervisory position based out of Bangalore. In his new assignment as a consultant, Kini will assist Bharti in enhancing customer service delivery.

 Taneja has decided to take on another assignment outside the company. 




